<p>Idaho presents exceptional opportunities for both solar panel installations and energy-efficient HVAC systems, making it one of the most attractive states in the Northwest for renewable energy investments. With an average of 4.9 sun hours per day, Idaho receives abundant solar radiation throughout the year, particularly in the southern regions where cities like Boise and Twin Falls enjoy some of the highest solar potential in the Pacific Northwest. The state's relatively low electricity rates at 10.2¬¢ per kilowatt-hour, combined with excellent solar resources, create favorable conditions for homeowners looking to reduce their energy costs through solar installations.</p>

