<p>Idaho's diverse climate zones present unique HVAC challenges that require carefully selected heating and cooling solutions. The state experiences a continental climate with cold winters and warm summers, though conditions vary significantly from the mild Snake River Valley to the harsh mountain regions. Boise and surrounding areas typically see winter lows of 20-30¬∞F and summer highs reaching 90-100¬∞F, while northern Idaho and mountainous regions experience more extreme temperature swings with winter temperatures often dropping below 0¬∞F.</p>

